<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>What&#39;s the proper way to set these? Executing xdg-ninja suggests to &#39;add it to your shell&#39;s configuration before setting any of the other environment variables&#39;.</p> <p>So, if I type &#39;export $XDG_CONFIG_HOME=path&#39; is it enough to have them after reboot, or is the proper way to add those lines into my .zshrc as well? Or how I&#39;m supposed to do these?</p> <p>I read the wiki: <a href="https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/XDG_Base_Directory">https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/XDG_Base_Directory</a> and the full specification: <a href="https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html">https://specifications.freedesktop.org/basedir-spec/basedir-spec-latest.html</a></p> <p>But I don&#39;t see actual examples of this.</p> <p>Edit. This is solved now. I&#39;ll add those lines into .zshenv.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Lord_Schnitzel"> /u/Lord_Schnitzel </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wfvm2s/how_to_set_xdg_env_variables/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wfvm2s/how_to_set_xdg_env_variables/">[comments]</a></span>